  <description>&lt;span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden"&gt;Chinese Studies&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-uid field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden"&gt;&lt;a title="View user profile." href="https://www.ub.bw/user/1" lang="" about="https://www.ub.bw/user/1" typeof="schema:Person" property="schema:name" datatype="" class="username" xml:lang=""&gt;webadmin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-created field--type-created field--label-hidden"&gt;Thu, 06/10/2016 - 15:38&lt;/span&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The number of the Chinese living in Botswana has increased. As  of 2009 Chinese formed the largest group of self-employment holders in Botswana. It is therefore the responsibility of the University of Botswana to bridge the cultural and language gap In Botswana. The Chinese Studies Programme is a window through which we hope our students will learn and explore issues around China.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Our programme is made up of two crucial components:  learning Chinese language and Chinese culture. The major of Chinese Studies focuses on history, culture. Beyond the courses offered in the Chinese Studies programme, students may choose an array of courses which include marketing, Language and literature courses, media studies, philosophy and religion and sociology.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Study abroad in Asia&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Our Student have the opportunity to spend a year in one of our partner universities in China. This will allow them to fully interact with the Chinese.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
